   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE GOD'S SPIRIT OF LIFE BECOMING THE WAY FOR US TO SERVE IN THE CHURCH LIFE Scripture Reading: Eph 4:4a; 1 Cor 12:1-11, 13; Rom 14:17; Eph 3:16-17, 19 OUTLINE God's Spirit of life being the essence of the church, the Body Eph 4:4a: We having been baptized into one Body in this Spirit as the essence 1 Cor 12:13a.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>We being made now to drink of this essential Spirit of God 1 Cor 12:13b.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>God's Spirit of life being the power in the church life Rom 14:17: For us to live in the reality of the kingdom.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>For us to live out righteousness and peace in joy.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God's Spirit of life filling the believers to become the church with the full-grown stature as the fullness, the expression of God Eph 3:16-17, 19: Strengthening the believers' inner man.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>That Christ may make home in the believers' heart.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God's Spirit of life as the source of all gifts and functions in the service of the church, the Body 1 Cor 12:1-11: As the Dispenser of all gifts.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>As the factor in all coordination.</S>
   </TEXT>
